<title>SOUTH AFRICA: TOLARAM 2000 POSTS YEAR LOSS, NO DIV.</title>
<headline>TOLARAM 2000 POSTS YEAR LOSS, NO DIV.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-03-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended Dec 31, 1996 </p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)	 </p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     33.3 loss   vs 39.9 profit</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 nil	   vs 5.0  </p>
<p>    Attrib income	   3.88 loss   vs 4.55 profit</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   3.90 loss   vs 4.62 profit</p>
<p>    Tax			 0.03	  vs 0.07</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   2.58	  vs 2.53</p>
<p>    Turnover		  69.81	 vs 84.38</p>
<p>Full name: Tolaram 2000 Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The textile firm said it was hit hard by the</p>
<p>inability of ageing plant and equipment to achieve desired</p>
<p>productivity. A 30 million rand investment is well advanced and</p>
<p>the new technology should solve many problems and restore</p>
<p>profitability.</p>
